Description: Wheel-made storage vessel sherd. Orange fabric with large white shell inclusions, coned pattern and painted decoration (blue and red).
Curator's comments: Parallel from El-Ashmunein (Bailey 1998, no. C710) decoration from a 9th-10 th century AD context ( but in a different ware).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IE.22)
